text: Pachasniyuq (Quechua pachas gypsum, -ni, -yuq suffixes, "the one with gypsum", Hispanicized spelling Pachasnioc) is a mountain in the Huancavelica Region in Peru, about high. It is situated in the Huaytará Province, in the west of the Pilpichaca District. Pachasniyuq lies southwest of Walla Q'asa and southeast of K'uchu Urqu. == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Huancavelica Region
